    {
        " survived to adulthood. Theodor died when Bormann was three, and his mother soon remarried.     Bormanns studies at an agricultural trade high school were interrupted when he joined the 55th Field Artillery Regiment as a gunner in June 1918, in the last days of ": null
    },
    {
        "World War I": "World War I"
    },
    {
        ". He never saw action, but served garrison duty until February 1919. After working a short time in a cattle feed mill, Bormann became estate manager of a large farm in ": null
