    },
    {
        " progressed, Hitlers attention became focused on foreign affairs and the conduct of the war to the exclusion of all else. Hess, not directly engaged in either of these endeavours, became increasingly sidelined from the affairs of the nation and from Hitlers attention; Bormann had successfully supplanted Hess in many of his duties and usurped his position at Hitlers side. Hess was concerned that Germany would face a war on two fronts as plans progressed for ": null
