        ", the strongest protest against a Nazi policy up until that point. Bormann and others called for Galen to be hanged, but Hitler and Goebbels concluded that Galens death would only be viewed as a martyrdom and lead to further unrest. Hitler decided to deal with the issue when the war was over.     ": null
